Class FormElementViewSelector

java.lang.Object
  org.araneaframework.jsp.support.FormElementViewSelector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class FormElementViewSelector
extends Object
implements Serializable

A class that holds information about the tag and the attributes of the tag that will be used to render the form element. It is mainly used AutomaticFormElementUtil

Author:
Jevgeni Kabanov (ekabanov@araneaframework.org)
See Also:
AutomaticFormElementUtil, AutomaticTagFormElementTag, Serialized Form

Constructor Detail

FormElementViewSelector

public FormElementViewSelector(String tagName,
                               Map<String,Object> attributes)
Creates a view selector for a form element (the latter is specified through AutomaticFormElementUtil). This object will only carry information about which tag (with attributes) to use.

The attributes for the tag are key-value pairs where key is a String (the name of the attribute) and value is any object (the value for the attribute).

The attribute names must qualify to appropriate setter of class AutomaticTagFormElementTag as: 

 set[attributeName]([AttributeValueType] attributeValue)

This constructor expects that the URI of the tag library is the same as for Aranea tag library!

Parameters:
tagName - The name of the tag (not a tag class name!) to use.
attributes - The attributes for the tag.
See Also:
AutomaticFormElementUtil, AutomaticTagFormElementTag

FormElementViewSelector

public FormElementViewSelector(String uri,
                               String tag,
                               Map<String,Object> attributes)
Creates a view selector for a form element (the latter is specified through AutomaticFormElementUtil). This object will only carry information about which tag (with its URI and attributes) to use.

The uri is the URI of the tag.

The attributes for the tag are key-value pairs where key is a String (the name of the attribute) and value is any object (the value for the attribute).

The attribute names must qualifify to appropriate setter of class AutomaticTagFormElementTag as: 

 set[attributeName]([AttributeValueType] attributeValue)

Parameters:
uri - The URI of the tag library.
tag - The name of the tag (not a tag class name!) to use.
attributes - The attributes for the tag.
See Also:
AutomaticFormElementUtil, AutomaticTagFormElementTag
